olive oil
1 eggplant
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet Slivered Almonds
2 clove garlic
1 radish
1 tomato
½ lemon
1 packet mint
1 packet couscous
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
¾ cup boiling water
1 packet Garlic Dip
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 tsp honey
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet diced bacon

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Boil the kettle.
• Cut eggplant into 1cm chunks.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over Nan's special seasoning, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
• In the last 5 minutes of roast time, crumble diced bacon over eggplant and roast until just golden, 5 minutes.

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic. Thinly slice radish. Slice tomato and lemon into wedges. Pick and thinly slice mint leaves.
• To a small microwave-safe bowl, add garlic and a drizzle of olive oil and microwave in 10 second bursts, until fragrant.
• To a large bowl, add couscous and vegetable stock powder.
• Add the boiling water (3/4 cup for 2P / 1 1/2 cups for 4P) and stir to combine. Immediately cover with plate and leave for 5 minutes.
• Fluff up with fork and set aside.

• In a small bowl, combine tahini, Greek-style yoghurt and a splash of water. Season to taste and set aside.
• When the eggplant and bacon is done, add the honey and toss to combine.
• To the couscous, add garlic oil, radish, tomato, mint, mixed salad leaves and a squeeze of lemon juice. Toss to combine and season to taste.

• Divide mint couscous between bowls.
• Top with smokey roast eggplant and bacon.
• Drizzle over tahini yoghurt dressing. Garnish with slivered almonds. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!